Commune Concilium tentum in Camera Guildhald ciuitatis London, decimo nono die Iunij, anno regni Dom. nostri Iacobi nune regis Angliæ ... whereas by a Common Councell holden the ninth day of Aprill, in the seuen and thirtieth yeare of the reigne of our late Soueraigne Ladie, Queene Elizabeth, an act was made, for the preuention of theft ... by establishing a registry to bee kept, of all the bargaines, contracts, sales, pawnes of plates jewels, goods ... City of London (England).
[3] leaves.
Printed by VVilliam Iaggard, London : 1622.
Caption title. Second part of title from first seven lines of text. Imprint from colophon. Reproduction of original in the Henry E. Huntington Library and Art Gallery.
